WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:05.823
This Core edition shows how to build a new client’s file from documents and other

2
00:00:05.823 --> 00:00:07.435
available source evidence.

3
00:00:10.641 --> 00:00:15.116
The first step records the incoming documents and where they came from.

4
00:00:18.322 --> 00:00:22.182
The second connects client identity with the people involved.

5
00:00:25.388 --> 00:00:29.701
The third organizes requested services and engagement facts.

6
00:00:32.907 --> 00:00:38.066
Open requests, actions, dates and history remain distinct but connected,

7
00:00:38.066 --> 00:00:42.939
so every fact can be traced to its source or the decision behind it.

8
00:00:46.145 --> 00:00:51.049
Each country maps its own documents, checks and rules onto this structure,

9
00:00:51.049 --> 00:00:54.892
producing a readable client file that shows what is known,

10
00:00:54.892 --> 00:00:59.200
what remains open and how the professional relationship develops.
